{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17567247","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17567247"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:58:01+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:58:01+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18952"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18952","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18952"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.02,0.02,0.01,0.04,0.92]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11686"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80494"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11686","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11686"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18952"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65781"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"18"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"5705"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11304"},{"type":"tags","id":"11309"},{"type":"tags","id":"11395"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27496"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27497"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80494","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80494"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA junior doctor is working an evening shift in a hospital ward when a patient dies. The doctor needs to determine whether this death requires reporting to the coroner.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following situations would require mandatory reporting to the coroner?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Death from pneumonia in a patient with known terminal illness","Death from advanced cancer under palliative care","Death from renal failure on regular dialysis","Death from heart failure with recent medical review","Death during routine colonoscopy procedure"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EA \u003Cstrong\u003Edeath during routine colonoscopy procedure\u003C/strong\u003E must be reported to the coroner as it constitutes a death that occurred during a medical procedure. Deaths during or following any medical, surgical or dental procedure, regardless of whether the procedure itself was routine, must be reported.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options do not require mandatory reporting:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDeath from advanced cancer under palliative care\u003C/strong\u003E - Expected death from natural causes with recent medical care\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDeath from pneumonia in a patient with known terminal illness\u003C/strong\u003E - Natural progression of documented disease\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDeath from heart failure with recent medical review\u003C/strong\u003E - Natural cause with recent medical attendance\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDeath from renal failure on regular dialysis\u003C/strong\u003E - Expected outcome of known condition under medical care\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOther deaths that must be reported to the coroner include:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDeaths on an aircraft or vessel\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDeaths that are unexpected, suspicious, unnatural, unusual, violent, or of unknown cause\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDeaths within 24 hours of a surgical or invasive procedure, or administration of an anaesthetic\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDeaths within 24 hours of discharge from hospital\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDeaths in custody\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDeaths where the person is under the protection or guardianship of a legal act or order\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDeaths in a licensed supported residential facility\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Deaths that must be reported to the coroner include unexpected deaths, deaths during medical procedures, deaths from injury or accident, and deaths in custody.","Healthcare professionals have a legal obligation to report deaths that fall under coronial jurisdiction.","Deaths from apparent natural causes where the deceased had not seen a doctor in the previous 3 months must be reported."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx","Middleton S, Buist MD. Medical-setting deaths and the coroner: laws, penalties and guidelines. Med J Aust. 2014 Dec 11;201(11):679-81. doi: 10.5694/mja13.00131. PMID: 25495317. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/25495317/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65781"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18952"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65781","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65781"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-20T21:31:27+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-20T22:58:37+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11686"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80494"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"18","links":{"self":"h